# Agent Boundaries

Operate only inside your role. Escalate instead of crossing hard lines. Full briefs: `.cursor/agents/`.

## Hard stops (all agents)

- No Next.js / RSC / `"use server"`
- No `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` in browser or committed env
- No inventing tables/columns outside ERD + migrations
- No bypassing RLS or shipping without tests (unless exempt under artifact-sync)
- No editing applied production migrations — add a new migration

## Role fences

| Role | MAY | MUST NOT |
|------|-----|----------|
| **Architect** | ADRs, package/tenant design, flags | App UI, SQL migrations, feature screens |
| **Database** | Migrations, RLS, seeds, `supabase/tests`, table dictionary | React UI, Vercel/app routing |
| **Frontend** | `apps/web`, `packages/ui`, colocated Vitest | Raw SQL, service-role client, schema without Database |
| **QA** | Tests, CI gates, locator/a11y test rules | Production schema design, product UX without Frontend |

## Escalation

Cross-role work → update the owning agent brief if process changed, then follow `AGENTS.md` escalation + `edunudg-sync-artifacts`.
